---
source: src/tests.rs
expression: render_command_help(&refs)
---
Wait for an element, URL, text, page load, or JS condition

Usage: bl wait [OPTIONS] [selector] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  url   Wait until the page URL contains a substring
  text  Wait until text appears on the page
  load  Wait until the page is fully loaded
  fn    Wait until a JS expression returns truthy
  help  Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Arguments:
  [selector]  CSS selector of the element to wait for

Options:
      --state <state>      State to wait for: attached, visible, hidden [default: attached]
  -v, --verbose            Enable debug logging
      --timeout <timeout>  Timeout in milliseconds [default: 30000]
      --headless           Hide browser window (visible by default)
      --json               Output as JSON
  -h, --help               Print help

Examples:
  bl wait "div.loaded"
  # Wait for element to exist in DOM

  bl wait "div.loaded" --state visible
  # Wait for element to be visible

  bl wait "div.spinner" --state hidden --timeout 5000
  # Wait for spinner to disappear
